  "text": "A localization of clathrin heavy chain to Hermes bodies of spermatozoa confirms an earlier study [CITATION_1] . Abundant SNAREs are characterized in the tethering, docking and fusion category (figure 6e; e.g. VAMP3, figure 6f ). Annexins are highly abundant, as are the AAA proteins p97 (see below), NSF and its associated alpha SNAP (figure 6e). The atlastins and reticulons, known to be involved in membrane curvature, tubulation and fusion [CITATION_2] , are also abundant in the Hermes body (figure 6e).",
